/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do not commit
# Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
# The path is rooted at the crate root so the fuzz/ subcrate's own
# Cargo.lock (a binary cargo-fuzz target) is committed for
# reproducible fuzzer builds.
/Cargo.lock
